results.name: Decimal expansion of Pi^(Pi^Pi).
reference: Christopher Creutzig & Walter Oevel, MuPAD Tutorial. Berlin: Springer-Verlag (2004): 339.
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 19..20000
program: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20100); x=Pi^Pi^Pi/10^18; for (n=19, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b073234.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, May 01 2009, corrected May 19 2009, had -n
